---
description: Docker and Docker Compose rules for local development
globs:
  - "**/Dockerfile"
  - "**/docker-compose*.yml"
  - "**/.dockerignore"
alwaysApply: false
---
- Keep services modular: frontend, backend, and db.
- Use service names for container-to-container communication, not localhost.
- Use named volumes for database persistence.
- Read configuration from environment variables.
- Keep Dockerfiles and Compose files simple and readable.
- Do not hardcode secrets in Docker or Compose files.
